      "content": "fair enough. but if u look at how these companies actually operate now, they basically control the entire digital infrastructure. if they been allowed to do this for years and it hasn't broken the economy, does that mean the \"innovation\" argument is kind of a smokescreen? like, isnt it more of a settled fact that they've become too big to allow anyone else to compete?",
